name: Planet Bluto
desc: >PLANET_BLUTO is a multi-media online creator that specializes in game development, web app development, 3D art, chiptune/electronic music production, and more

name: PixelzwithaZ
desc: PixelzwithaZ is a visual artist who makes 3D models and rig and does decent rig animation, as well as being a musical artist using Beepbox and a game dev using Godot

name: Discoholic
desc: Discoholic is musical artist and DJ who does everything disco, funk, and house related- with a hint of VGM influences- whether it’s old school or new wave, as well as a twitch streamer with a high energy personality that does DJ sets and other fun events

name: Flyann
desc: Flyann is a youtuber/twitch streamer and visual artist turned game dev who uses a game engine for their stream layout to make it more interactive, introducing an MMO called “Fly Online” that can be played in twitch chat

name: SupaBubba
desc: SupaBubba is a musical artist who makes VGM with rich soundscapes, inspired insturmentation from SNES and retro FM, and composition that makes you wanna groove

name: Star Garden
desc: Star Garden is a game being developed by GameGarage with an early 2000s vibe that features has the mechanics of raising a creature like Chao Garden in Sonic Adventure, and then the gameplay of City Trial in Kirby Air Ride, with music done by Qteku

name: FLAKS
desc: FLAKS is a musical artist who makes deep electronic tunes  with rich soundscapes and an emphasis on hard hitting beats and bass heavy instrumentation

name: CubeNatural
desc: CubeNatural is a musical artist with an early 2000s vibe who makes tunes that explore genres such as jungle, house, and breakcore as well as being a visual artist who does expressive character designs, comics, and also 3D modelling

name: METAROOM
desc: METAROOM is a musical artist who makes tunes with interesting soundscapes and an incredible understanding of instrumentation, sampling, and rhythm that explores various genres, vibes, and moods

name: MEMODEMO
desc: MEMODEMO is an electronic musical artist who specializes in upbeat, energetic, and nostalgic tunes spanning various genres such as future bass, drum’n’bass, and digital fusion

name: AQUASINE
desc: AQUASINE is a musical artist who makes internetcore tunes with heavy chiptune/VGM inspirations and jazzy compositions with deep understandings of rhythm. He also does pixel art and 3D models for cover art, as well as being a developer himself!

name: JC
desc: JC is a musical artist who makes sample based tunes that reminds you of early 2000 DJ sets and has done work for games such as Pizza Tower- as well as currently working on their own game KIPIDON, a stylized 3D cute shooter about making people feel love again!

name: AIA
desc: AIA is a game dev and twitch streamer who has an interactive stream layout and is currently working on a game called Mana Valley, a casual open world RPG that features a magic system and farming simulation

name: Hayd_n
desc: Hayd_n is a visual artist and game dev who makes stylized 3D models and rigs and is currently working on a rhythm based beat’em’up that

name: RasterPlan
desc: RasterPlan is a visual artist who does impressive spritework, detailed character designs, and really well stylized 3D models and rigs

name: Tohomoko
desc: Tohomoko is a musical and visual artist that makes chiptune and VGM music in Beepbox with rich compositions and also does traditional drawing and neat character art as well as dabbling in game development as well

name: PracticalNPC
desc: PracticalNPC is a game dev and Twitch streamer who’s currently working on a game called Memori, a tight and fast precision platformer

name: Mordecai
desc: MDXCAI is a game dev, visual artist, and twitch streamer who uses the Unity game engine for their stream layout for more interactive streams, and portrays the world of Kyomi- the dark purple and rainy realm caught between life and death- through his works

name: Qteku
desc: Qteku is a musical artist who makes nostalgic tracks with  an early Y2K aesthetic, featuring genres like jungle, drum ‘n’ bass, house, and techno

name: NME64
desc: NME64 is a twitch streamer and game dev who uses Godot for game dev as well as stuff like their interactive stream layout and website

name: Maidmage
desc: Maidmage is a visual artist who does really stylized character models and rigs, recently having more of a Y2K aesthetic

name: Grynmoor
desc: Grynmoor is a visual artist who does intricate robot character designs and stylized 3D models and rigs- as well as a pixel artist who is working on ways to merge both mediums

name: Chubbs
desc: Chubbs is a visual artist who does really good work for character designs

name: MEAT
desc: MEAT is a visual artist and game dev who does really good work for character designs as well as very passionate about lots of media

name: iDogedochiptune
desc: iDoge is a chiptune/digifu musical artist who uses Blubox (a mod of Beepbox made by Blu) to make really chill & nostalgic jams with beautiful soundscapes and impressive compositions

name: SubiCat
desc: SubiCat is a (sometimes chiptune) musical artist and pianist who uses Beepbox to make pleasant tunes with really nice compositions

name: Devious
desc: Devious is a musical artist known in the Beepbox scene for his jazzy compositions with a range of styles and instrumentations, even dabbling in other programs

name: Answearing Machine
desc: Answearing Machine is a musical artist who makes ‘music for tryhards’ in Beepbox that is electronic adjacent and feature intricate drum compositions due to their drummer background

name: Alwaysalty
desc: Alwaysalty is a visual artist who makes intricate drawings of various creatures, as well as a musical artist occasionally who makes cool electronic music using Beepbox

name: Karma
desc: Karma is a software engineer/programmer who’s also a classically trained pianist who uses beepbox and other softwares

name: Lognes
desc: Lognes is an artist who creates hard chiptune rock music in beepbox and various types of other visual arts. He is also one of the developers of ProjectHTTP who does visuals, sounds, and game feel!
